        "content": "<p>alexcrichton <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12427#issuecomment-3819281174\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12427\">PR #12427</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Semi-blocked on <a href=\"#narrow/channel/217126-wasmtime/topic/Is.20anyone.20using.20.60WasmStr.60.20or.20.60WasmList.3CT.3E.60.20as.20a.20guest.20return/with/570861394\">https://bytecodealliance.zulipchat.com/#narrow/channel/217126-wasmtime/topic/Is.20anyone.20using.20.60WasmStr.60.20or.20.60WasmList.3CT.3E.60.20as.20a.20guest.20return/with/570861394</a></p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 570861422,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1769709274
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12427#issuecomment-3819302328\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12427\">PR #12427</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>In discussion with @dicej on this we see 1 of two paths forward:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Delete <code>Func::post_return</code> as a Wasmtime API. This would mean that post-return is always called automatically, and that'll untangle some internals to avoid the panics happening here.</li>\n<li>Fix the internals, probably by making them a bit more complicated, and keep <code>Func::post_return</code> as-is.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>We're currently thinking of pursuing (1) here pending if anyonoe has use cases on Zulip.</p>\n</blockquote>",
